ete checkout 4. Check email for access codes\t5 tool access confirmations 2\tSetup Reclaim\tReclaim\t1. Sign up with Google 2. Connect calendar 3. Set work hours 9-5 4. Create \"Bundle Integration\" habit\tCalendar blocks appear 3\tEvaluate Project Scope\tAll Tools\t1. Define project complexity (1-10) 2. If 1-5: Use EasySite first 3. If 6-10: Use Bolt.new 4. If speed critical: Use Emergent\tClear tool selection 4-7\tBuild MVP\tChosen Tool\tEasySite: Drag-drop interface Bolt: Natural language prompts Emergent: One-click generation\tWorking prototype Phase 2: Integration Layer (Days 8-14) Integration Priority Matrix: Priority\tIntegration Type\tPica Setup\tBusiness Impact\tImplementation Time HIGH\tPayment Processing\tStripe + PayPal\tDirect revenue\t2-3 hours HIGH\tEmail Marketing\tConvertKit/Mailchimp\tLead nurturing\t1-2 hours MEDIUM\tCRM Connection\tHubSpot/Salesforce\tCustomer management\t2-4 hours MEDIUM\tAnalytics Tracking\tGoogle Analytics 4\tPerformance insights\t1 hour LOW\tSocial Media APIs\tFacebook/LinkedIn\tContent automation\t1-2 hours Phase 3: Polish & Optimize (Days 15-21) Conversion Optimization Checklist: Mobile responsive design (test on 3 devices) Page load speed under 3 seconds Clear call-to-action buttons (test 3 variations) Lead capture forms above the fold Social proof elements (testimonials, logos) Exit-intent popups (increase conversions by 15-30%) Phase 4: Launch & Scale (Days 22-30) Go-Live Protocol: Pre-Launch (Days 22-25) Set up monitoring (Uptime Robot, Google Analytics) Configure backup systems via Hostinger Test all payment flows end-to-end Prepare launch sequence emails Launch Day (Day 26) Deploy to production domain Activate all integrations Monitor for 24 hours continuously Send launch announcements Post-Launch (Days 27-30) Collect user feedback Optimize based on analytics Plan next iteration Document lessons learned 🔄 Advanced Integration Scenarios Scenario A: Framer-Quality Design Pipeline Tools Integration: EasySite.AI → Bolt.ne